<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<h2>Minor</h2>
<p>The minor in Geographic Studies is defined by its concern with place. Geographers strive to answer spatial questions regarding the Earth’s surface; to describe and explain the character of regions; to ascertain the ways in which historical and contemporary humans have used and shaped the Earth’s surface; and to understand the interactions of physical, biotic, and human systems within our global environment. The minor is compatible with a variety of environmental majors in the college.</p>
<p>The minor is sponsored by the Department of Human Ecology, <a href="/departments-programs-degrees/human-ecology/landscape-architecture-bs/">Landscape Architecture &amp; Environmental Design Program</a>.</p>
<h3>Minor Advisor</h3>
<p>David De La Pena; see academic advisor <a href="mailto:gerdman@ucdavis.edu" target="_blank">Galyna Erdman</a> in 1331 Hart Hall.</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
